                    <comment id="12322354" author="daniel.naber@t-online.de" created="Sat, 30 Apr 2005 05:53:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This has recently been fixed in the development version, i.e. the fix will be &lt;br/&gt;
part of Lucene 1.9. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12322355" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 30 Apr 2005 12:23:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Charles, are you using the QueryParser to convert a String into a Query?  If so,&lt;br/&gt;
that&apos;s the problem... when parsing a RangeQuery, the endpoints aren&apos;t run&lt;br/&gt;
through the analyzer, so they would end up not matching the terms in the index&lt;br/&gt;
that were analyzed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12322356" author="jakarta@ehatchersolutions.com" created="Sun, 1 May 2005 05:45:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A workaround for pre-Lucene 1.9 is to subclass QueryParser and override&lt;br/&gt;
getRangeQuery to lowercase the begin and end terms.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
